{
  "text": "\u2022 Although the probability of contagion is tamed by a heterogenous degree distribution, the conditional extent of contagion (i.e. the fraction of failed banks in those cases where at least 5% of the system has gone down) is not significantly different with respect to the case of a homogeneous degree distribution. In particular, the robust yet fragile behavior highlighted in [CITATION_1] is preserved.",
